        <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="collapsibleNavbar">
            <ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" href="/#portfolio">Portfolio</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>
    <div class="waContainer">
            <h1 class="mainHeader">Origin Weather App</h1>
            <p class="pInfo">A web app for weather searches. Always know if you'll need an umbrella! </p>
            <a class="mkLink" href="https://fa-weather-app.herokuapp.com">See It Live Here</a>
            <div class="upperContainer">
                <div class="builtInfo">
                    <p>Built with:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Express</li>
                        <li>ReactJS</li>
                        <li>NodeJS</li>
                        <li>Redux</li>
                        <li>OWM API</li>
                        <li>Bootstrap</li>
                        <li>& more...</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <img src="./views/public/weatherapp.png" alt="Image of Project">
            </div>
            <div class="signupInfo">
                <p>Every day should fell like paradise, but unfortunately it doesn't always work out
                     that way. Enter your city or where you will be visiting to see if you will
                      need sunscreen or an umbrella. 
                     On "Go!", an Axios HTTP request is sent to the OpenWeatherMap (OWM) API,
                      which returns weather data to display based off the city. A history of recent 
                      searches with the city and time of search is stored and displayed on the right.
                      It looks like on this day you would need a umbrella in Tokyo.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="imgContainer">
                <img src="./views/public/waSearch.png" alt="Image of Project">
            </div>
